/SSLEngine.html#setHandshakeApplicationProtocolSelector(java.util.function.BiFunction)\\n      chosen.orNull\\n    }\\n\\n    engine\\n  }\\n\\n  private def chooseProtocol(protocols: ju.List[String]): Option[String] =\\n    if (protocols.contains(H2)) Some(H2)\\n    else if (protocols.contains(HTTP11)) Some(HTTP11)\\n    else None\\n\\n  def applySessionParameters(engine: SSLEngine, sessionParameters: NegotiateNewSession): Unit =\\n    TlsUtils.applySessionParameters(engine, sessionParameters)\\n\\n  def clientSetApplicationProtocols(engine: SSLEngine, protocols: Array[String]): Unit = {\\n    val params = engine.getSSLParameters\\n    params.setApplicationProtocols(Array(\\\"h2\\\"))\\n    engine.setSSLParameters(params)\\n  }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1781129407421}}\n433:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying paths for context**\\n\\nI’m looking at the concept of CWD and how it relates to forge_worktrees, which are nested. The source context path mentioned in the prompt seems to refer to an absolute path with the structure .../forge/local_repositories/source_context being a sibling to forge_worktrees. It looks like I need to differentiate between this and cwd/local. I need to be specific and ensure I read the absolute path correctly.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_09934c5d992f21e6016a29e0bcdea4819085f545a46abb4c67\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqKeC_n17cuQkKHMAsP87d04C7Yh7x7I_1OVAmZDvXIsfNYNvc8SW5QoMgHH7zK_39QsS2QetxwQD6uGaCr6RA9AyosVQMGFw9heAFvvt4dq3E4xMrfbU6mB_U_ORBmXmT6vqg4_GqNMD0REjtNxAeHVKqtBvMrMzYtwQYiE_nBMxqwNyzts6Pn58z8Zx7lvIJrJ6vmh4-mSPKxpqeep0XS5JToY3hmo_Rkog2l1fcqx_AdYDQJYAvOHi-unS1fjMx6qyo-CGfkB_E2RmiEdKHaDZ_eVUFU9l-RajfxYO44hvi_jVh6gG7c8dtF3l5YAxoSHuFZ4NLJCImrw-Wsrs1yd1tR-gkU3_WaePvS45IYpqZh4jhE5ii3zbgortWZhdaxZu3HJMffCWfnLt_Kk7G_Ge-5kioMKDqfbtOy_G7GB8rx0D