ttp-core will pull in the required pekko-stream. It seems like the source compile may need that too!\\n\\n**Investigating dependencies and configurations**\\n\\nI’m looking into how Gradle handles dependencies, especially concerning the \\\"provided\\\" scope from Maven. It seems like \\\"provided\\\" may not be included transitively at runtime, or perhaps it’s not even compile-time. If I use types from the stream in tests, I might need to manually add a dependency, as the existing build doesn't include pekko-stream. I should also find public APIs in pekko-http-core that expose HTTP2 over TLS configuration for Http2AlpnSupport. I’ll search for references.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_09934c5d992f21e6016a29e0f11bcc819098fdf0fde5527f7b\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqKeEBjTwD7wDbhRDfG9Rl-nR7ZX3a9i0fLYtb1T86cmA3GukDYK9HWbwB-JjTJqs92vgseR-Z-1XHQpu5Y13h_XjBbrl5G2Pw-v3jjGVLZRfrLyaz3TjwFyE3XXPVYlIxm8f4D_0hrKtlhP0PFJhVtwMQW56q2c1BaIrbbh9Hk9dEZW18LkYUDiD4KeDJSxFtPb_iqJVIQP_8cQUOMI_0XtqPyUDFc_vcAbbIDzywc3nIHzP2wKrlImGfZhh-MZKNDhFAyu72NGvBnvxDkXG13Ma9sJZFi7Tbfk4xaazzFGvX7l5NcvI64n88R-y56KudtrLuhMAGLXYh5aaWz9okwv5seoH0QusWyZbFQLibJrMUNTRhnoIa19-MYwwTty_1th9q84B4Vz8S9FvacVaH_cUCE86VhYDW7RQlEFI1yPLl_Wo-NpdoXt0mGQfOlZ2Dq5oPEfbxwJCQvCrgeYfL-LriNF_WYR-JiyVRCORRCAnerwhGVjBqZIGcGxh5xKoIA4ahkVfaBhUaJlDVeuZQ3Gjd2j_smoLRdEIo3QCunstL7Udw2QWyCtWlwqaxCeWJvLmkcNr_8xkYXX2I0K3nfrqgXndpX7_Wgd3ipa_W9j3KT9_JsLkcfTG2wi0VQVmxaaBWT5zYuwtQgHupb6Rw-R_kDJZzxCEoBJ5Q1eGlAkmnxTm9aYZz9hEmt-JXNNYr-pB4oWzqpXsKU_UW8PI8D4uiTeFRMYQLo_8gGUX2jM7QjncflqelGvuRTjmE2gXieHpfKrP8gBzarYyeV_HHsRytRjhgU_StzPAU68dWQH8oClZpr5w1pBlJn7s7NXv6F3DignadAeM429KQlKVKvJOBnMvU2gIhs1YfIhjtasf0UyvAw_IbxHkkQ5OQ9l4FerMb1HM9rGSjT9Q2O0QA0u8yc66lD172DWk57ghGR-G4njR30i8VfmYhzSCeCNLXtyf40O7MwgE8diRPOAuOtI_zV1pWzS-8xU3ymMG896I1OfS0XJQVRUYYJURNhrkfo9I7szuXWELNf_Rm59Uysk8_YRbHgmmXYzKs4sACl1zPf8z8Tkc9ZZq8zX7MGt2zvLyDjVTOXZP1NUNBeLi5hNIASOwdEwrnM4p-LVEk-c_ggEaupmwdZwj3wx